                  <additions>
                     <t:list xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">
                        <item xml:id="a0_357">
                           <locus target="#Throughout">-Throughout</locus>
                           <q xml:lang="ar">Ǧuz’ markers consist of various circles in black: single, single with dot, double, double with a dot, quadruple, quadruple with dot. Some markers have the word ǧuz’ written either inside the circle or outside. Ṯumn markers in black.
</q>
                           <desc>Drawings / Decorations</desc>
                           <note/>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2_357">
                           <locus target="#668r">-668r</locus>
                           <q xml:lang="ar">The drawing consists of letter combination m-h drawn in a form of a cross. </q>
                           <note>The symbol is often used in amulets. The drawing is placed after the heading of the sūra.</note>
                           <note>
                              <q xml:lang="ar"/>
                              <term key="Magic" ana="#Magic"/>
                           </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3_357">
                           <locus target="#672v">-672v</locus>
                           <q xml:lang="ar">Pentagram </q>
                           <note>The symbol is often used in amulets. The drawing is placed after the heading of the sūra.</note>
                           <note>
                              <term key="Magic" ana="#Magic"/>
                           </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a1_357">
                           <locus target="#658v">-658v</locus>
                           <q xml:lang="ar">The marginal note consists of Arabic letter forms or resemble them. The letters appear drawn rather than written and the letter combinations are unreadable. The only word that can be easily read is Allāh in the lower end of the framed area. The text could be a copy of an amulet.</q>
                           <note>
                              <q xml:lang="ar"/>
                              <term key="Magic" ana="#Magic"/>
                           </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4_357">
                           <locus target="#37r-58v-68v-103v-199r-222r-255v-272v-281r-295v-327r-360v-494v-541r-586v-595v-596r-599r-615r-627r-637r-639v-652r-661v">-37r, 58v, 68v, 103v, 199r, 222r, 255v, 272v, 281r, 295v, 327r, 360v, 494v, 541r, 586v, 595v, 596r, 599r, 615r, 627r, 637r, 639v, 652r, 661v</locus>
                           <q xml:lang="ar">Various forms of circles: single, double, quadruple, in blue and red. Some of the marking the end or beginning of a sūra. The circle on fols 596r and 627r contain a cross.</q>
                           <desc>Drawings / Decorations</desc>
                           <note/>
                        </item>
                     </t:list>
                     <t:list xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#18v">-18v</locus>
                           <q>اغثنا سيد ابادر سيدي \ عليكم رحمة القادر مددي \ اغيتوا قطب الناحية سيدي ...ا</q>
                           <note>Additional verses to the main poem invoking Šayḫ Abādir.</note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#Inner lining of the back cover">-Inner lining of the back cover</locus>
                           <q/>
                           <note>Notes in Fidel script</note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#Inner lining of the front cover">-Inner lining of the front cover</locus>
                           <q/>
                           <note>Note in Fidel script</note>
                        </item>
                     </t:list>
